@page "/createcharacter/lavender"
@using Components.Buttons
<h1>The Soft Lavender Luminary</h1>
<div>
    <MyButton ButtonText="Back To Color Choices" OnClick="ReturnToColorChoices" />
    <MyButton ButtonText="Choose Lavender" OnClick="ChooseLavender" />
</div>
<div  class="grid-container" style="max-width:100%;height:auto;">
    <div class="grid-item">
        <h4>Kin: The people of Este</h4>
        <p>Este is the Valar known for healing and rest. As one of her followers, you possess a calm and restorative aura.</p>
        <p>The color soft lavender, reminiscent of healing herbs, represents your soothing and restorative nature.</p>
        <p>You excel in healing magic and are able to restore both body and mind.</p>
        <p>Inherent strengths:
            <ul>
                <li>You can heal injuries and cure ailments with your touch. +10% health restored per touch.</li>
                <li>Your presence is calming, often diffusing tense situations. +2 Wisdom when talking instead of fighting.</li>
                <li>You possess the ability to induce restful sleep, even in the most troubled minds. +2 Willpower when using sleep or dream spells.</li>
                <li>You recharge your magic by going out alone and meditating.</li>
            </ul>
        </p>
        <p>
            Inherent weaknesses:
            <ul>
                <li>Your powers are less effective in chaotic or corrupted environments. -3 Willpower when the level of chaos is too high.</li>
                <li>You require periods of solitude to rejuvenate your own energies.</li>
                <li>Direct combat can be draining, making you rely more on your allies for protection.</li>
            </ul>
        </p>
        <h4>Starting Stats</h4>
        <ul>
            <li>+5 Willpower (WP): Represents mental fortitude and resistance to magical corruption.</li>
            <li>+3 Wisdom (WD): Indicates knowledge of lore, understanding of nature, and strategic thinking.</li>
            <li>+3 Agility (AG): Determines speed, reflexes, and ability to navigate terrain.</li>
            <li>-1 Strength (ST): Reflects physical power and endurance.</li>
        </ul>
        <div>
            <MyButton ButtonText="Back To Color Choices" OnClick="ReturnToColorChoices" />
            <MyButton ButtonText="Choose Lavender" OnClick="ChooseLavender" />
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="grid-item" style="max-width:100%;height:auto;">
        <div>
            <img src="images/este.jpg" alt="Este" />
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

@inject NavigationManager NavigationManager
@code {
    private void ReturnToColorChoices()
    {
        NavigationManager.NavigateTo("/createcharacter");
    }
    private void ChooseLavender()
    {
        NavigationManager.NavigateTo("/createcharacter");
    }
    
}